column17: Alex Cebulski, Rob White, Emily Haughton
column78: New clear glycol griffin mixed.
column110:
Installed GNSS mount
Installed snow stakes
Batt voltage very low at station. Looked at log of failed tx and voltage drops to 10.2 on tx. Solar panel was not covered with snow on arrival. Solar panel reading 22V with full sun which is equal to open circuit voltage on the back. 
So likely not problem with solar panel. 
Unplugged batt cable and hooked up batt charger running from gene charged for about 4 hours. Batt read 11.5 before charge and 11.9 after. 

Consider bringing replacement batt on next visit.
